comments: Aldridge (SAS) makes marginal contact with Carter (ATL) off-ball in the post that does not affect his ability to defend.
[Observable in enhanced video] Collins (ATL) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Carter (ATL) makes contact to Aldridge's (SAS) arm during his shooting motion on his jump shot attempt.
White (SAS) has a marginal resting hand to Young (ATL) and doesn't affect his SQBR or knock him off of his direct path to the basket.
White (SAS) maintains a legal guarding position as Aldridge (SAS) cleanly blocks Young's (ATL) driving shot attempt.
Huerter (ATL) has a marginal resting forearm that he does not extend to DeRozan's (SAS) body during his driving shot attempt.
Collins (ATL) sets the pick in Gay's (SAS) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Gay (SAS) puts a marginal hand to Young (ATL) that does not affect his SQBR or knock him off of his direct path to the basket.
White (SAS) maintains a legal guarding position on Young (ATL) during the drive.
Huerter (ATL) makes contact with Aldridge (SAS) off-ball that does not affect his ability to get to the pass.
[Observable in enhanced video] Aldridge (SAS) fails to fully clear the lane within three seconds.
DeRozan (SAS) wraps Young (ATL) during the inbounds off-ball.
Aldridge (SAS) makes marginal contact to the body of Len (ATL) during his shooting motion that does not affect his play at the basket.
Carter (ATL) moves laterally into the path of White (SAS) in transition and the contact affects his SQBR.
[Observable in enhanced video] Young (ATL) gathers the ball and comes to a jump stop, then moves his pivot foot heel to toe to create distance.
Gay (SAS) has a marginal resting hand to Young (ATL) that he quickly releases during the driving shot attempt.
